HEADWORD: allotrophic
<hw>al`lo*troph"ic</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧l`l⟦osl⟧*tr⟦ocr⟧f"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>'a`llos</grk> other +
<ets>trophic</ets>.]</ety> <sd>(a)</sd> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>Changed or modified in nutritive power by the process of
digestion.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Plant Physiol.)</fld> <def>Dependent
upon other organisms for nutrition; heterotrophic; -- said of plants
unable to perform photosynthesis, as all saprophytes; -- opposed to
<contr>autotrophic</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
